\p THEY that are in Jerusalem and those who are in Judea and the senate and Judas, to Aristobulus, king Ptolemy’s teacher, who is also of the stock of the anointed priests, and to the Jews that are in Egypt, send greeting and health.
\v 11 Having been saved by God out of great perils, as men arrayed against a king, we thank him greatly.
\v 12 For himself cast forth into Persia those who arrayed themselves\add against us \add* in the holy city.
